==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brush wheel
<hw>Brush" wheel`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>A wheel without
teeth, used to turn a similar one by the friction of bristles or
something brushlike or soft attached to the circumference.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A circular revolving brush used by turners,
lapidaries, silversmiths, etc., for polishing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brushwood</ent>⟦br⟧
